<DOC><DOCNO> AP880615-0013 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-15-88 0656EDT</FILEID><FIRST>d a PM-BRF--HatSentence     06-15 0121</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Hat Sentence,0124</SECOND><HEAD>Man Given 10 Years For Stealing 36 Hats</HEAD><DATELINE>JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A thief who was tracked down by policefollowing his four-block trail of stolen hats was sentenced to 10years in prison.   The sentence imposed Monday on 27-year-old Lavon King was doublethe state-prescribed guideline.   Circuit Judge David C. Wiggins said King was a habitual offenderwith a long criminal record.   King was convicted May 24 of the March break-in of Heyman'sDepartment Store.   When King and another man were spotted outside the store bypolice, they began running and tossing away the hats they hadstuffed under their shirts. A trail of 36 hats led police to King.The other man was never arrested.</TEXT></DOC>